title: Wall Street Breakfast April 25: French Stocks, Euro Stumble After Macron Victory in France
author: Seeking Alpha
dc:creator: Seeking Alpha
description: In a replay of the 2017 election, France's Emmanuel Macron has defeated candidate Marine Le Pen. Semiconductor companies are on tap to be in the spotlight following what has been a tumultuous start to the year. The U.S. pledged another $322M in military financing to help Ukraine. Catch the WSB article here.
